Favored Terrain		KEY:Favored Terrain ~ WORLD WALKER		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Archetype.DruidArchetype	DESC:At 3rd level, the world walker gains the ranger's favored terrain ability (Core Rulebook 65). She treats her druid level as her ranger level for this ability. If she has levels in both classes, both class's levels stack for determining the effect of this ability. This ability replaces trackless step and reduce nature's lore.																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.43
Path of Trees		KEY:Path of Trees ~ WORLD WALKER		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Archetype.DruidArchetype	DESC:At 9th level, once a day, a wanderer can step within a tree and then teleport from that tree to another one in a manner similar to the tree stride spell (Core Rulebook 362). She gains an extra use of this ability each day at 12th level, and a third use of this ability at 15th level. Furthermore, a world walker of 13th level or higher can use this ability to teleport to any other tree of its type up to 100 miles away. This ability replaces both venom immunity and timeless body.																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.43




